    {
      "key": "descri",
      "label": "Description",
      "controlledVocab": false,
      "searchable": true,
      "value": "Title taken from slide mount. View of a sign outside Alyeska Resort. The sign reads: \"Kobuk Valley Jade Co. We take our name from the beautiful valley where the jade is found. In the center of Kobuk Valley, 150 miles north-east of Kotzebue, is the famous Jade Mountain. The jade is shipped down the Kobuk River by barge. The boulders you see were shipped over 2,000 miles. We make all our jewelry from this jade. From the Eskimos we get our ivory and other handcrafts. We have on display a unique collection of northwest Alaskan artifacts. Everyone is welcome. We hope our shop will add to your knowledge and enjoyment of Alaska.\"",
      "controlledVocabList": null
    },
